HEADWORD: Doomsday
<hw>Dooms"day`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>d<?/mes
d⟦amac⟧g</ets>. See <er>Doom</er>, and <er>Day</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A day of sentence or condemnation; day of death.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧My
body's <xex>doomsday</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The day of the final judgment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I could not tell till <qex>doomsday</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Doomsday Book</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Domesday
Book</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doomsman</ent>⟦br⟧
